				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hey KAAOS, long time no see.
<br />

<br />
Have you guys heard of Realms of Torment yet? <a href="http://www.realmsoftorment.net" target="_blank">http://www.realmsoftorment.net</a>
<br />

<br />
The game's supposed to be released this year, but there hasn't been much hype about it and it's not even listed on ebworld.com. 
<br />

<br />
"Constructed as a full PvP-based title, it will provide flexible combat and magic systems as well as a impressive arsenal of weapons, armours and magic items." 
<br />

<br />
The world will be full pvp, and it looks really in depth as far as crafting/combat/etc... Dev's on the forum mentioned that knowledge = power, and pvp will be based on skill more than items like UO (i never played it so i can't say i know how it worked). They also have aging, a bloodline system and permadeath.
<br />

<br />
Just throwing it out there for you guys. Wheeeeeeeeeeeeeeee.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
