			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't remember if this particular game was what prompted me to write that article but yes that's basically what the article is about. People are designing "PvP" games yet the combat system isn't even spelled out while the majority of the game is entering it's "polishing" phase. They don't spell it out because they haven't even thought about it themselves typically. 
<br />

<br />
Yes I know it's not to those extremes it's just that I find it amazing that people who are developing a "PvP" game put so much thought, effort, and resources into the overall "world" and the plethora of features they are going to offer and yet their PvP combat system isn't even close to being finished, usually it's not even really touched until everything else is done. 
<br />

<br />
The world, the features, the game itself should be fleshed out around a PvP combat system. All creatures, gear, features, economy, "world building" and whatever other bullshit they want to come up with should be designed around end game PvP combat. 
<br />

<br />
I still think someone should build a "combat code" and sell it out to people building games much like the FPS fucks did with 3D graphic engines.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.kaaos.com/sigs/azmosig.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
